{"TopicId":148883,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Show me your KER HUD layout","CreatedByName":"SkyKaptn","CreatedById":153990,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T00:18:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SkyKaptn","CreatedById":153990,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T00:18:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore info is good info. This is how I have made my HUDs in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0I think there are 7 HUDs, reasonably categorized:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/uHEaySi\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uHEaySi.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022uHEaySi.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T00:20:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AlZX3B4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AlZX3B4.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I have other atmospheric and manoeuvre displays that are not shown here. Moar info!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T01:19:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the additional information I need. Node burn time 1/2 shows below the last separator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kAQx7T6.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kAQx7T6.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T01:20:28Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 01:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyKaptn","CreatedById":153990,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T01:26:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222778840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475111971\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022regex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, regex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNode burn time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever thought of that one since it is displayed in stock. Installed that asap since stock always shows N/A or something completely wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T01:52:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222778849\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475112375\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SkyKaptn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, SkyKaptn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever thought of that one since it is displayed in stock. Installed that asap since stock always shows N/A or something completely wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E does good math.\u00A0 It will even tell you when to start your burn, which is more than just 1/2 the burn time before the node.\u00A0 It takes into account the mass of the spent fuel as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMine looks almost just like \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70807-regex/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002270807\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70807-regex/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@regex\u003C/a\u003E but I split the staging off into it\u0027s own group on the other side.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EEDIT: Well I guess I do have a few more items, I like to see the \u0022Time To \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0022 at a glance as well and I have Impact Biome which doesn\u0027t show here.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022e3iDZnp.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/e3iDZnp.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T02:07:35Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 02:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Psycho_zs","CreatedById":137644,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T11:43:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLow on screen real estate, so taking most of it. Orbital, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E budget, biome and landing essentials.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot66.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/attachments/22639/screenshot66.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyKaptn","CreatedById":153990,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T13:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222779357\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475149384\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137644\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Psycho_zs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Psycho_zs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLow on screen real estate\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to change the font size. There is even a HUD button for that under misc tab. (aswell as settings in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E. I think you must be in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E for the latter)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Stole your suicide burn btw \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FancyMouse","CreatedById":142946,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T14:35:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022E2Jenbq.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/E2Jenbq.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScreenshot taken a while ago, not specifically for this purpose, so quite a few unrelated stuff but idea is there. Maneuver info entries aren\u0027t shown here but it\u0027s supposed to be in the panel right of the altimeter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty proud of this layout and \u003Cem\u003Eevery single\u003C/em\u003E info is needed for me to fly a ship, and I already have a habit of looking a specific area of my monitor when looking for any information :-(\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Francois424","CreatedById":98138,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T16:28:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI merely use this, very compact mode\u00A0:\u003Cbr\u003E\n(It also include suicide burn and impact time when landing, but I was in orbit when I took the screenie)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022snQI6AA.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/snQI6AA.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoboRay","CreatedById":46556,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T21:29:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00220ZTuCC9.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/0ZTuCC9.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s less on the left side so that the HUDs don\u0027t overlap the science uplink reports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd there\u0027s probably a situational thing or two missing off the right side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T21:33:49Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 09:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by RoboRay\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Trann","CreatedById":83801,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-29T23:34:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTop-left is orbital details. \u00A0Top-right is ship details. \u00A0Bottom-left, and always with the nav ball,\u00A0is surface/touchdown details.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have a\u00A0rendezvous HUD (not seen) that\u0027s set at the right-mid edge which I use for the rare satellite positioning (angle, relative inclination,\u00A0period).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fggTuZs.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/fggTuZs.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFun topic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-29T23:34:44Z\u0022 title=\u002209/29/2016 11:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Trann\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T20:57:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLeft to Right top row: DeltaV info / Orbit / Default Altimeter / Situation\u00A0info / Vessel\u00A0targeting\u00A0\u0026amp;\u00A0switching. Below the Altimeter I switch between a\u00A0rendezvous HUD and\u00A0a landing HUD.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022OpDtzni.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/OpDtzni.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-30T21:06:23Z\u0022 title=\u002209/30/2016 09:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by tjt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cantab","CreatedById":104935,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T21:04:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI keep mine pretty slimmed down and close to the default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/p/JBjGhd\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Cute little baby rocket\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm8.staticflickr.com/7364/27966709132_58164d1984_b.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy most notable addition is \u0022Situation\u0022 under \u0022Biome\u0022, to help know when to run science experiments, and I added the \u0022Critical Thermal Percentage\u0022 HUD in the middle because my shuttle is thermally limited on ascent and sometimes re-entry too. I sometimes add a few more parameters to the orbital section too. But if I want more detailed info, such as burn time for manoeuvres or radar altitude for landings, I use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-30T21:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222781720\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475269498\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022104935\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cantab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, cantab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI keep mine pretty slimmed down and close to the default. \u0026lt;SNIP\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy most notable addition is \u0022Situation\u0022 under \u0022Biome\u0022, to help know when to run science experiments, and I added the \u0022Critical Thermal Percentage\u0022 HUD in the middle because my shuttle is thermally limited on ascent and sometimes re-entry too. I sometimes add a few more parameters to the orbital section too. But if I want more detailed info, such as burn time for manoeuvres or radar altitude for landings, I use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting that you and I made most of the same choices for the center HUDs (same order and everything). I don\u0027t use Mach number because I almost exclusively fly rockets. Also agree that the Situation readout is so useful for science collection\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-30T21:08:54Z\u0022 title=\u002209/30/2016 09:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by tjt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-01T12:55:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222778897\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148883\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221475113962\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 29.09.2016 at 3:52 AM, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003EKER\u003C/abbr\u003E does good math.\u00A0 It will even tell you when to start your burn, which is more than just 1/2 the burn time before the node.\u00A0 It takes into account the mass of the spent fuel as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s even better - it takes necessary staging into account.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSay, you\u0027re in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E with 200m/s remaining in a Twin Boar left over from launch; the rest of the 900m/s burn will need to come out of an LV-N on the transfer stage. Start your burn about a second early, because it doesn\u0027t include the time between the Boar switching off, staging and starting the Nuke. But the rest of calculation is correct.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-01T18:32:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t know about the burn time readout..that\u0027s a great tip. Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}